  "summary": "This standard formalizes ZKMeta, a minimal interface for contracts that verify or depend on zero-knowledge proofs. It defines how to expose a proof-system identifier, circuit identifier, circuit version, public-input schema (hash and URI), and verification-key URI. The goal is to enable interoperable wallet, relayer, explorer, rollup, and dApp tooling without prescribing any specific proof format.",
